  https://www.sqlite.org/

  SQLite is in the public domain. The author disclaims copyright to the SQLite
  source code. In place of a legal notice:

    May you do good and not evil.
    May you find forgiveness for yourself and forgive others.
    May you share freely, never taking more than you give.

  FinGrind vendors SQLite 3.53.0 through the official SQLite3 Multiple Ciphers
  2.3.3 amalgamation and builds managed native SQLite libraries from that
  source for Gradle, Jazzer, CI, and container runtime surfaces.

  FinGrind does not bundle a native SQLite library inside the CLI JAR itself.
  Standalone JAR execution uses Java 26 FFM with either
  `FINGRIND_SQLITE_LIBRARY` or a compatible host `libsqlite3` that exposes the
  same SQLite 3.53.0 / SQLite3 Multiple Ciphers 2.3.3 contract.

